## Push Summary — skrptiq-cli (main)

### What shipped
Hierarchical autocomplete — typing `/` now shows only top-level commands. Subcommands appear only after selecting the parent:

1. `/` → `/help`, `/run`, `/hub`, `/profile`, `/mcp`, ...
2. Select `/hub` → `list`, `search`, `import`, `update`
3. Select `/profile use` → shows profile names from DB

Three stages: command → subcommand → argument. Each level filters as you type.

Command registry restructured with `Subcommands` field on `Command` type. ArgProviders can live on either commands (e.g. `/run`) or subcommands (e.g. `/profile use`).

### Tests
- `go test ./...` — all passing
- `go vet ./...` — clean
- Comprehensive tests: top-level only at stage 1, subcommand filtering, arg via subcommand, NeedsMore signalling
